              BIOL 532 Developmental Neurobiology Seminar (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-18912" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Biology (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Biology (Sci)              : Discussions of all aspects of nervous system development including pattern formation, cell lineage, pathfinding and targeting by growing axons, and neural regeneration. The basis for these discussions will be recent research papers and other assigned readings.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Donald Van Meyel, Artur Kania, Alyson Elise Fournier (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Winter</li>
              <li>1 hour lecture, 2 hours seminar</li>
              <li>Prerequisites: BIOL 303 or BIOL 306 or permission of instructor</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
